ZH: 我用绳子把自行车拴在树上。
EN: I tied the bicycle to the tree with a rope.

ZH: 他把狗拴在院子里。
EN: He tethered the dog in the yard.

ZH: 这只猫不喜欢被拴着。
EN: This cat doesn't like being tied up.

ZH: 妈妈把围裙拴得很紧。
EN: Mom tied the apron tightly.

ZH: 我把帽子拴在柜子上了。
EN: I hang the hat on the cabinet.

ZH: 他希望能把那个坏习惯拴住。
EN: He wishes to break that bad habit.

ZH: 她在身上拴着一个丝带。
EN: She wore a ribbon around her body.

ZH: 这个地方没有地方能拴绳子。
EN: There's no place to tie a rope in this area.

ZH: 我们需要一个拴狗的地方。
EN: We need a place to tie up the dog.

ZH: 请拴好安全带。
EN: Please fasten your seatbelt.

ZH: 这家餐厅提供地方给客人拴马。
EN: This restaurant provides a place for guests to hitch horses.

ZH: 拴紧你的书包，不然会掉下来。
EN: Tie your backpack tightly, or it will fall off.

ZH: 把绳子拴在柜子的把手上。
EN: Tie the rope to the handle of the cabinet.

ZH: 拴住门，不要让风吹开。
EN: Tie the door, don't let the wind blow it open.

ZH: 他被拴在椅子上，无法动弹。
EN: He was tied to the chair, unable to move.

ZH: 房子外面有个拴马的栅栏。
EN: There's a hitching post outside the house.

ZH: 这条小船拴在码头上。
EN: The small boat is moored at the dock.

ZH: 把绳子拴紧，以免船漂走。
EN: Tie the rope tightly to prevent the boat from drifting away.

ZH: 请拴好你的行李，以免丢失。
EN: Please secure your luggage to prevent any loss.

ZH: 老板要求员工把自行车拴在指定的地方。
EN: The boss requires the employees to tether their bicycles in the designated area.
